Inferno, loyal as always, immediately followed Hydras&#39; orders. He
stayed with Hydras, always attempting to keep himself between him
Hydras and Tankor, his optics glowing watchfully. The fuzors on the
other hand were not so happy with the orders. There were a few
grumbles and angry faces, but they generally complied with Hydras as
well.

Terrorsaur just looked at Tarantulus for a moment as if sharing some
internal thought, but then, like the others they appeared to follow
suit, lowering weapons and readiying to follow.

&quot;Me no like Tank-bots.&quot; Waspinator said, some how voicing the opinion
of many, as he glanced at the many muzzles that seemed to be pointed
in his direction. He sighed as he stood next to Hydras.

&quot;Good choice.&quot; Tankor said after Hydras gave his commands to the his
soldiers. Tankor gestured to the other tank drones with him, and they
circled around like soldiers guarding some sort of convoy. &quot;Come.&quot;
Tankor said as he too shifted into vehicular mode. Several tanks
positioned themselves infront of Hydras&#39; crew while others were
behind, tankor beside them.

(OOC: Assuming that Hydras does follow . . . )

